    "description": "Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025 Racket - Power and Precision for Professional Offensive Play. This Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025 racket redefines power and precision on the court. Designed with a diamond shape and a high sweet spot that offers the perfect balance between power and control, this Adidas racket is made for professional or intermediate level players who master technique and want an explosive racket with total control on every shot.. It features a new 6K aluminized Carbon design that provides controlled power to compete consistently, and a core with EVA Soft Performance rubber that delivers a more comfortable impact and a smooth ball exit.. Its technologies include the Octagonal Structure, the Low Poly design, the Spin Blade Decal, a relief that enhances the feeling of control and allows generating more spin on the ball, and a weight of 360-375 grams that offers stability and firmness without sacrificing maneuverability. In short, it is the perfect racket for players seeking maximum power in smashes and maximum stability on every impact, dominating the point from any area of the court with complete confidence.. Technical Features of the Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025. The Adidas Metalbone Carbon 2025 has been designed for players who prioritize power on every shot and need maximum precision in defensive moments. The racket stands out for its diamond shape with a high balance that facilitates connection with overhead balls. Let's look at its features in detail:. Brand: Adidas. Model: Metalbone Carbon 3.4. Year: 2025. Shape: Diamond. Balance: High. Weight: 360-375 gr.. Core: EVA Soft Performance. Faces: 6K Carbon. Surface: Rough. Playing Level: Advanced. Playing Style: Power. Advanced Technologies and Materials of the Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025 Racket for Superior Performance. Octagonal Structure: Tubular Frame for Maximum Precision. The Octagonal Structure features a carbon frame with a carefully designed octagonal section to reduce twisting and achieve more precise shots. This tubular carbon frame with an octagonal section maximizes stability on every shot, providing precision and firmness even in demanding situations.. Low Poly: Polyhedral Design for Greater Rigidity and Power. The Low Poly polyhedral design features a racket frame and core with polyhedral geometry that adds structural rigidity, delivering greater rigidity and power in shots. This is essential for players seeking explosive power with the ability to execute decisive shots when needed.. Extra Power Grip: Extended Grip for Greater Inertia. The Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025 incorporates the Extra Power Grip (EGP). This is a longer-than-usual grip that increases leverage, resulting in greater inertia and power in aerial shots with less effort, producing a more stable and powerful impact. The Extra Power Grip is ideal for shots like volleys, viboras, or smashes and perfect for offensive players looking to maximize power in their attacks.. 6K Carbon: High-Quality Carbon for Exceptional Durability. The faces of the Metalbone Carbon made with 6K carbon provide a solid feel and offer the exact balance between control and power, along with outstanding durability. The 6K Carbon planes guarantee a solid response, greater durability, and a clean hitting sensation, which is essential for players seeking a racket that delivers clear feedback on every shot.. Soft Performance EVA: Comfortable Core without Sacrificing Firmness. The core of the Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025 incorporates EVA Soft Performance rubber. This rubber offers a softer and more comfortable touch without sacrificing good ball exit, making it perfect for players who want controlled and precise shots on every point.. Additionally, one advantage of the EVA Soft Performance is that its softer touch provides greater comfort for players by helping reduce some of the vibrations generated on impact. Although its density is lower, it does not compromise power because it is combined with 6K Carbon, offering the ideal balance between power and aggressiveness with a more comfortable hit.. Spin Blade Decal and Smart Holes Curve: Precision in Lifted and Cut Effects. The Adidas Metalbone Carbon incorporates two technologies focused on imparting more spin with less effort: the Spin Blade Decal and the Smart Holes Curve technology. On one hand, the Spin Blade Decal is a 3D relief that increases surface roughness, helping to enhance spin on shots, even on the most demanding hits.. On the other hand, the Smart Holes Curve technology consists of the intelligent distribution of holes on the racket with a curved arrangement that improves grip on the ball upon contact with the surface.. These two combined technologies are perfect for players seeking a racket that not only performs well in attack but can also offer unpredictable shots with spin to your opponent, adding a technical advantage on the court.. Structural Reinforcement: Perimeter Reinforcements for Maximum Durability. The Structural Reinforcement incorporates strategic reinforcements that prevent twisting, which is essential to maintain the racket's reinforced stability on every shot. This technology guarantees the racket's durability and improves shot consistency, offering a uniform response across the entire surface.. Diamond Shape and High Sweet Spot: Maximum Power in Attacks. The Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 features a diamond shape combined with a high balance (weight in the head of the racket) that makes this racket the ultimate offensive tool. Having the weight at the top favors aggressive play and allows executing sharp and precise attacks from the net more easily.. Who Is the Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025 Padel Racket For?. The Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025 is designed for:. Padel players with advanced and intermediate levels who master attacking technique and want an explosive racket with total control on every shot.. High-performance players seeking maximum power in smashes.. Offensive players looking for extra precision and impact.. Players seeking the ideal combination of power, control, and comfort.. Intermediate players with a technical base in attacking play who want to advance and perfect their level with a diamond-shaped racket.. Frequently Asked Questions about the Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025 Racket. Is the Adidas Metalbone Carbon 2025 suitable for intermediate players?. Yes. Although the Adidas Metalbone Carbon 2025 is designed for advanced level players who master technique and want an explosive racket with total control, it can also help intermediate players improve and perfect their attacking technique.. What advantage does the Metalbone Carbon's Octagonal Structure offer?. The Octagonal Structure reduces twisting to achieve more precise shots. This tubular carbon structure is designed to keep every shot clean and defined, resulting in firmer and more precise hits even in demanding situations.. Conclusion: The Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 Is the High-Performance Racket You Need to Dominate with Power and Precision. The Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025 is the ideal choice for those who want to elevate their performance without sacrificing feel. Its combination of intelligent rigidity, explosive power, and technical control makes it the perfect ally for offensive players seeking extra precision and impact.. With high-quality materials such as its 6K Carbon surface and EVA Soft Performance rubber core, and technologies specifically designed for professional players, it guarantees exceptional performance on every point.. If you are a player with an offensive style and are looking for a padel racket that combines diamond shape, explosive power, absolute precision, and comfort in hitting, the Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025 is your best option. Don’t miss the chance to take your Adidas Metalbone Carbon 3.4 2025 and dominate your rivals with confidence and comfort!",
