    "description": "Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 3.4 2025 Padel Racket - Absolute Control and Professional Precision for Superior Defensive Performance. This new Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 3.4 2025 racket redefines control and precision on the court. Designed with a round shape and medium balance that offers absolute control with an extra attacking edge, this Adidas racket is made for professional or intermediate level players who master technique and want a racket with total control on every shot.. Regarding its technical features, it incorporates a 6K Carbon surface that provides an extra dose of controlled power to consistently return balls, and a Soft Performance EVA core that delivers a more comfortable impact and a smooth ball response.. Among its technologies, the Low Poly design stands out, a polyhedral structure in the frame and heart of the racket that provides greater rigidity and power on every hit, along with the Spin Blade Decal, a textured relief that enhances the feeling of control and allows more spin on the ball, among other cutting-edge technologies detailed below.. Technical Specifications of the Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 3.4 2025. The Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 3.4 2025 is a racket designed for players who prioritize absolute control on every shot and require maximum precision. The racket features a round shape with medium balance. The round shape places the weight closer to the handle (unlike diamond-shaped rackets), and the medium balance allows an extra boost of power when needed. Its technical specifications are as follows:. Brand: Adidas. Model: Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 3.4. Year: 2025. Shape: Round. Balance: Medium. Weight: 360-375 gr.. Core: Soft Performance EVA. Faces: 6K Carbon. Surface: Rough. Playing Level: Advanced. Playing Style: Control. Advanced Features and Technologies of the Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025 Racket. Octogonal Structure: Tubular Frame for Maximum Precision. The Octogonal Structure features a carbon frame with a carefully designed octagonal section to reduce torsion and achieve more precise shots. This tubular carbon frame with an octagonal section maximizes stability on every hit, providing precision and firmness even in demanding situations.. Low Poly: Polyhedral Design for Greater Rigidity and Power. The Low Poly polyhedral design presents a racket frame and heart with polyhedral geometry that adds structural rigidity, delivering greater rigidity and power in shots. This is essential for players seeking explosive power with the ability to execute decisive shots when necessary.. Extra Power Grip: Extended Handle for Greater Inertia. The Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 3.4 2025 incorporates the Extra Power Grip (EGP). This is a longer-than-usual grip that increases leverage, resulting in greater inertia and power in aerial shots with less effort, producing a more stable and powerful impact. The Extra Power Grip is ideal for shots like volleys, viboras, or smashes and perfect for offensive players looking to maximize power in their attacks.. 6K Carbon: High-Quality Carbon for Exceptional Durability. The faces of the Metalbone Carbon Ctrl are made of 6K carbon, providing a solid feel and offering the perfect balance between control and hitting power, along with outstanding durability. The 6K Carbon planes ensure a solid response, increased durability, and a clean hitting sensation, essential for players who seek a racket that transmits clear sensations on every shot.. Soft Performance EVA: Comfortable Core without Sacrificing Firmness. The core of the Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 3.4 2025 incorporates a Soft Performance EVA rubber. This rubber offers a softer and more comfortable touch, providing greater comfort for players by helping reduce some of the vibrations generated on impact. Although its density is lower, it does not compromise power because it is combined with 6K Carbon, offering the perfect balance between control and comfort with power.. Spin Blade Decal and Smart Holes Curve: Precision in Lifted and Cut Effects. The Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 3.4 includes two technologies focused on imparting more spin with less effort: the Spin Blade Decal and Smart Holes Curve technology. On one hand, the Spin Blade Decal is a 3D relief that increases surface roughness, helping to enhance spin on shots, even on the most demanding hits.. On the other hand, the Smart Holes Curve technology consists of the intelligent distribution of holes on the racket with a curved arrangement that improves racket grip upon contact with the ball on the surface.. These two combined technologies are perfect for players seeking a racket that not only performs well in attack but can also deliver unpredictable and spin shots to your opponent, adding a technical advantage on the court.. Structural Reinforcement: Perimeter Reinforcements for Maximum Durability. The Structural Reinforcement incorporates strategic reinforcements that prevent torsion, essential for maintaining the racket's reinforced stability on every shot. This technology guarantees the racket's durability and improves shot consistency, offering a uniform response across the entire surface.. Round Shape and Medium Balance: Maximum Control in Defensive Play. The round shape of the Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025 provides the advantage of shifting the weight closer to the handle, which favors defensive play by improving control during hitting. This round shape is combined with a medium balance that allows extracting an extra boost of power, ideal for attacking the opponent with more powerful shots.. Who Is the Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025 Padel Racket For?. The Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025 is the perfect choice for:. Advanced and professional players who compete frequently and play with a defensive strategy. Professional players who seek great control without sacrificing a solid and energetic ball response. Players who believe control and defense from the backcourt is the strategy to dominate points. Players in the improvement phase who master control and want a racket that supports them at a competitive and advanced level.. Frequently Asked Questions about the Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025. Is the Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025 exclusively for high-level players?. No. Although the Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025 is designed for advanced level players, its round shape, medium balance, and Soft Performance EVA core make it a perfect racket for intermediate players looking for a tool to improve and perfect their defensive technique.. What is the difference between the Metalbone Carbon and the Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025?. The main difference is that the Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025 padel racket is designed with a round shape, ideal for players seeking total and absolute control. On the other hand, the Metalbone Carbon is a diamond-shaped racket focused on offensive and attacking play.. Conclusion: The Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl Is the Ally You Need to Dominate with Absolute Control. The Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025 is not just a control racket: it is a precision tool that allows you to dominate the game strategically, with an extra dose of power and outstanding rigidity.. With high-quality materials such as its 6K Carbon surface and Soft Performance EVA rubber core, and technologies specifically designed for professional players to unleash controlled and precise shots, this racket guarantees exceptional performance on every point, allowing you to focus on executing control shots with maximum precision and confidence.. If you are looking for a padel racket that offers total control, absolute precision, and an extra boost of power thanks to its medium balance, the Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025 is your best option. Discover the Adidas Metalbone Carbon Ctrl 2025 and experience how your game evolves with every shot!",
